The paper discusses the use of nanopublications as a Linked Data format for scholarly data publishing, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The focus on provenance and metadata suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB), while the use of nanopublications for granular atomic information snippets and the analysis of large datasets suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also discusses querying and accessing the nanopublication dataset, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and semantic web (cs.SI).
